                        <h1>Where Did My Tooth Enamel Go?</h1>
                        <p>There are many reasons to want to whiten your teeth &ndash; but before you look at the how, let&rsquo;s look at why you got to this place.</p>
                        <p>Tooth enamel is a finite substance that can be worn down by foods, drinks, and smoking. The sugar in soda, for example, clings to the teeth and begins wearing down the enamel if not removed regularly. In fact, sodas amount for the biggest cause of tooth enamel erosion.</p>
                        <p>There are a few distinguishing features to tooth enamel:</p>
                        <ul>
                        <li>It&rsquo;s the hardest stuff in the human body.</li>
                        <li>At its thickest, it&rsquo;s just 2mm.</li>
                        <li>It can be colored yellow, white or hues of blue or gray.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Enamel is a mineral which means it can not grow back. Thankfully it&rsquo;s a tough substance, but it&rsquo;s not immune to erosion.</p>
